Brest Dynamo has protested against refereeing in a match with Shakhtar
An open letter was published to the Department of Refereeing and Inspection.

04 Nov 2019, 13:56

The Brest Dynamo has published an open letter on its website to the Department of Refereeing and Inspection of the ABFF, writes tut.by.
Dynamo Brest Football Club asks you to comment on the gaming moments related to the refereeing decisions that affected the outcome of the Dynamo Brest - Shakhtar match on November 3, 2019.
Please consider the following episodes:
Goal Khvashchinsky in the 24th minute into the goal of Dynamo Brest (possibly offside at the time of transfer);
Khoblenko’s fall in the 29th minute of the match as a result of contact with a Shakhtar player in the penalty area;
getting the ball into the hand of Shakhtar player Burko at the moment of breaking through towards the goal of Gordeychuk in the 80th minute;
cancellation of Pavlovc’s goal against Shakhtar in the 88th minute (offside).
